Stop by this quaint cafe and immerse yourself in the pleasant atmosphere of plant and human life. I always stop for a cortado when I’m nearby, also looks like great food, plants, and cbd products for your pleasure.
Best vegan chocolate chip muffins and coffee in NYC. You can’t cancel that! Namaste 🙏🏻
I had a good experience to come here to drink my coffee and eat my crunchy toast between bright atmosphere and cute 🪴

i love the atmosphere and all the plants but most of the drinks are related to south asians ingredients and the worker is white, feel like them stealing the culture from another group. also the drinks tastes absolutely horrible.
Fantastic Coffee. Great place to stop for any espresso beverage.
It's so beautiful with all the plants, place is very inviting and Avocado toast is good

I would not recommend this cafe. Poor food quality but the owners are truly the problem. They are some of the worst human beings every. Supporting this cafe means supporting slumlords who treat people badly. They have tremendous turn over of staff because they are mean.

I’m vegan and I’ll never eat here because the owner is a slum lord (see the New York magazine article) and is not good at customer service on top. Even before I knew that, I didn’t go too much because the food is meh for the price.

Quality, truly delicious food 👌  Edit: I used to really enjoy going to this place until I found out the owners are also owners of a building where many vulnerable people were evicted from their homes in the middle of the pandemic.
I love their cold brew.

Planted cafe has a lovely outside/inside environment. One is surrounded by a plethora of assorted lovely flowers and other fauna as they dine. There is a courtyard in the back yard for seating, as well as a few tables out front for some lovely people/dog watching. The menu is gluten free, vegan, and most importantly delicious!
Leaves a horrible taste in my mouth!

This business is ahead of the curve. Where else can you get organic food and drink, and have an apothecary and plant-shop right next door? The staff are always amicable and responsive, and I'd submit that the owner's attitude, which others have derided, helps Planted Cafe be a better cafe.
Terrible service. Manager kicked me out because of my crutch, which she was apparently concerned would scuff up the floor (that's not a thing). Very strange experience, would not recommend.
Bad quality for the price. Definitely won’t visit again.

Like, SO bad. Waaaay overpriced. Terrible people.

Won’t be going back ever. Food just seemed poor quality for what your paying you’d expect better. I can have tomatoes that taste better from Wendy’s. The owners seemed to have an attitude problem but the employees were great. After I left I found out how the owners treat other people and I’m just appalled I even went there and spent my hard earned money supporting such a terrible person. Making me think twice before I put in more research to the business I am spending my hard earned money on
Letting people (slumlords) work here without wearing masks is gross.
I walked by and the place looked cute.  Got avo toast but for the price, it wasn't great and ingredients didn't seem that fresh.  Probably won't try anything else.
Garbage food, garbage people
Terrible food and terrible vibes!
Overpriced bland foods

Planted cafe is quite possibly the best cafe I have ever stepped foot in. Their vegan rancheros are consistently delicious and their darling smoothie is fantastic. In addition to that, they have scenic backyard seating and as many plants as you could wish to buy. The owners are also very charismatic and caring towards the customers. The owners daughter is also mad cute. Overall, incredible restaurant and a 5/5 in my book.
Good food and nice owner

Came here for the first time since quarantine and was surprised with how much the quality has declined. Both my friend and i ordered the egg sandwich and it tasted like they dumped an entire container of salt on it and was definitely not worth $10 each. Also was not greeted by either owner inside. Didn’t even bother with a smile or hello. Just walked right passed us. Afterwards - I learned about the owners actions as landlords and evicting tenants illegally. I was so excited to find this place as it reminded me of a little Bali cafe but unfortunately will not be returning.
Rude owner & bad food.
not sure why this place only has 3 stars? Truly delicious & plant-based. Ordered via Caviar. So excited to have discovered!

So I just ate a few bites of my food and was surprised how badly they could eff up a macro bowl. Just overall unappetizing, not fresh, pretty bland. So I looked them up and was not surprised they’re abusive landlords. Mad I didn’t look them up before I ordered, but somewhat validating that their food matches their character. Def not dissing the employees. Bad business begins and ends with bad owners. Don’t support them!
don't go here... food made me sick
This place seems quaint at a glance, but the prices are through the roof and is less than welcoming to say the least. I would not recommend going here.

I was super on the fence about the place because of the price point and the unwelcoming attitude. Then I found out about the owners actions. I will not be subsidizing illegal evictions with my hard earned money.

Poor service, I was given the wrong order 30 minutes late. I advise you to stay clear of this place, floor and tables looked unsanitary too.
This place gives me bad vibes. Not a moral company and overpriced everything "trendy"
Most of the items are decent definitely not worth coming and spending money here. Would not recommend, would recommend just going to the deli down the block and gettin something there.

I used to come here a lot because it was close to my old job. The staff and clientele are typically nice people, and the backyard is relaxing but I’ve had my fair share of run ins with people there (employees and clientele) who clearly make me feel as though I don’t belong. This is a white, thin, wealthy place and they make no effort to be inclusive or welcoming to anyone outside that bubble at all. Besides that their food is prohibitively experience and pretty hit or miss, sometimes things are beautifully presented and taste great and sometimes they’re messy and the veggies taste a little old. In particular I’d avoid anything with cherry tomatoes in it.
the planted huevos rancheros are amazing!!!
Really cute interior with great vegan food and drinks and a play area in the back for kids, but I was super disappointed that my $5 iced tea was tiny and mostly ice.

This place is super snobby. The manager was condensending when I tried to return a product. I literally came to return it 2 hours after purchase. CBD is confusing and the product I bought had thc in it. I returned it because of that reason. The manager spoke down to me like I was a child. I will never return. So disappointed in the way I was treated. This happened in August and I am still upset.

I loved planted Cafe sooooo much! They had the best vegan breakfast I've had in such a long time: coconut yogurt parfait and avocado toast. Everything was made with love and it was so fresh! I also enjoyed the bright atmosphere, all the plants, not to mention the comfy seating. They have a little play area for the kids in the back as well. Planted was a happy, welcoming place I hope to return to soon.
Amazing menu and lovely ambiance!
Delicious vegan food! Beware that the store next door advertises as vegan but does have products with beeswax/honey (not vegan).
I had the veggie burger. I normally don't like mayonnaise based sauces but this sauce complimented the burger well. Planted is also very cozy and homie.

Lovely cozy cafe with delicious food! So many cafes have food as an afterthought but there is clearly someone who knows what they're doing in the kitchen here! We were very impressed with both the rancheros and the tortilla soup. Idk how they make the cashew cheese but it's amazing! We thought the prices for portions were quite fair, especially considering it's all made in house.  The space is very lovely and we appreciated that they have specific tables for laptop workers and tables reserved just for diners. Everyone can be happy! There's even a kids space in the back with toys and things to play with.  Everyone on staff was very nice and helpful. Definitely recommend this place and we'll certainly be back.

A DISGRACE! I don’t easily give low ratings, but this place is really a case of “the emperor’s new clothes” story. The space is nice, however, the food is tiny and super expensive! A Hummus “toast” will get you a tiny slice of bread with a teaspoon of hummus, one cherry tomato and a leaf of parsley for $7.90!!! Unacceptable!

Okay, so many things to say: first, ridiculously over priced. parfaits are delicious though I don't think any parfait is worth 12$. + bottle deposit. 2.) Their coffee I must admit is very delicious. 3.) environment friendly, they use mostly paper, glass jar and wooden eating utensils. Oh, lastly! Got a veggie burger, wasn't hot nor warm? Very hot (spice wise) though my actual burger was not. HUGE BUMMER WHEN UR WAITING 10 MINUTES!!!
(Translated by Google) Very atmospheric cafe! Delicious food and coffee! 😃  (Original) Очень атмосферное кафе! Вкусная еда и кофе! 😃
Love the ambiance. Unfortunately they were out of the jackfruit tacos which I was hoping to try so  I ordered the forbidden rice bowl and turmeric latte.

Great vegan cafe. They have a ton of vegan options. Also, an inviting place to come and work. Plenty of outlets built into the tables and plenty of seats. Vegan options are not an afterthought here. No oat milk though. Delicious coffee.
Great food that's good for you!

I come to this place five days a week every morning because I Iike the quality of food even though it’s very little and expensive. I pay $9 for smoothie and I have always problem getting it ( small baby cup or glass ) to go in medium cup . This place doesn’t have large cups. What they call large is small or extra small.  Never coming back again .
Cozy vegan cafe, open seating. Had a strawberry smoothie. So refreshing.

AMBIANCE ✔️ GREAT DRINKS ✔️ Great staff ✔️ great vibe✔️ awesome clientele ✔️ great VEGAN food✔️ outdoor seating ✔️ welcoming✔️ restroom ✔️ beautiful plants✔️ want to go again✔️ Went with two friends for lunch and we all loved it, lost track of time, didn’t want to leave.
(Translated by Google) Location really cute, baby friendly, with a very nice inner courtyard.  (Original) Endroit vraiment très mignon, baby friendly, avec un cour intérieure très agréable.

This is a great, unique little spot in the neighborhood. Only place I know in the neighborhood that has fresh Kombucha on tap which they also sell in growlers (love that!). They also have a great selection of CBD products, good coffee and a very cute ambience with a cool little backyard. Everyone who works at Planted is also very friendly. Would definitely recommend.
What an incredible spot! Great ambience in the place and the food is delicious. The cold brew smoothie is a must-try.

(Translated by Google) The cafe is in a beautiful location and is inviting: especially on a sunny day, this is a great place to linger. The service was extremely friendly.  However, the food cannot convince. I lack the finesse and I don't think it's cheap for what it is. I would love to come back, but then more for a coffee.  (Original) Das Cafe ist schön gelegen und wirkt einladend: gerade an einem sonnigen Tag ist das ein toller Ort, um hier zu verweilen. Die Bedienung war ausgesprochen freundlich.  Das Essen kann allerdings nicht überzeugen. Da fehlt mir die Finesse und ich finde es für das, was es ist, nicht gerade günstig. Ich komme gerne wieder, dann aber eher auf einen Kaffee.

I feel like it’s terrible business and bad karma to advertise a side salad and give less than ten pieces of lettuce with no dressing. I get it healthy food is good is expensive, but this place just feels like it’s a rip off. With 15% tip my lunch was almost $20 for a veggie burger and some lettuce on the side.

I stepped into this cafe and immediately felt at home. All vegan, mostly GF and PLANTS!! The atmosphere is chill and they played great soulful hip hop music when I was there. I ordered a superfood latte and brownie which came up to be around $12, expensive for what I received (small portions), but the vibe was so right. Good place to work and ground yourself.

I’ve been here three times and each time I’ve been majorly impressed with their coffee drinks. Their homemade cashew milk makes for a particularly rich and delicious yet delightfully simplistic latte. However, I ordered a simple breakfast dish  (eggless, meatless rancheros) and it took nearly 40 minutes for them to bring it out. No one else in the cafe had ordered food, and it certainly wasn’t crowded by any means or busy. I’ll be back for the delicious latte, but I won’t order food here again.
It has a very start-up energy to it. Lovely atmosphere and employees, I would recommend the red quinoa bowl or the homemade hummus...everything is so fresh and just a joy to eat.
Amazing selection of vegan food. I tried the red quinoa salad and a chia pudding. Quiet place, good for working on your laptop.
Everyone here was super nice. I had a chocolate chia pudding; the chocolate part is made with avacado, and I normally hate avacado, but it was really good!

Happy hour is a myth (or curated lie to attract patrons). I was very disappointed when I asked about it and practically laughed at like, no we don’t do that. Ok, then don’t promote it. Two stars because the chocolate smoothie was pleasant even if service and intentions were not.

It’s kind of crazy how much everything costs here. I’ve bought chai latte, ginger tea, smoothie, croissants. The ginger tea I will say is it’s saving grace and somewhat priced fair at $5 with a free refill. However everything else is $$$, I figured a small smoothie for $7 would be the average sized small of most cafes and smoothie places in manhattan. When it came out of the back kitchen it was literally kid sized. I want to like this places food options but between the prices and the homemade alternative milk recipes that need a bit more tweaking, I think I’ll pass from purchasing again. The atmosphere, convenient location and ginger tea are its’ only saving grace.
If you’re looking for a beautiful girl to serve you a delicious iced coffee that might have CBD oil in it, head to Planted Cafe. Great vibe, great service and a great product. I’ll be back.
I appreciate the relaxing music, magazines, ginger tea, and chia chocolate pudding. Great way to start the day! Would love to see a punch card system to reward regulars.
Great spot! The blueberry muffin tasted just like the ones my grandmother used to make, but vegan! Plus, this is the only place I can find a delicious real beetroot mocha in NYC. Highly recommend <3

Getting there! Great concept... CBD focused comfy cafe and co-working space. amazing that everything is vegan,GF, DF. it really makes a difference. Though my brownie tasted kinda blah, it's rare that I can go somewhere and order food safely. I'll definitely be ordering more as their menu matures. Also, that you can get a squirt of CBD in your coffee and pick up a nice pre rolled is a pretty good draw. Though one visit, a barista got really snarky with my follow up questions about their cbd products and he couldn't recall the name of their supplier farm or describe their "signature" drinks to save his life. My other visits, I was helped by a woman with great energy who volunteered a bunch of information and made me a really nice latte. Great potential--will be back and can't wait to see how they grow.
Matcha Cashew milk latte is worth the wait. I also love the CBD gummies. Really sweet addition to the neighborhood.
Vibrant flavors and a relaxing atmosphere make this quaint comfy cafe feel like what you wish home was like.
Employee with nose ring was nasty and one of the most rude people i have met.
Okay
Coffee shop + cbd

Planted feels truly focused on people rather than just selling product. Their house made milks are great and they were generous with their time in answering questions. The vegan muffins were not the the best I've had, but got the job done. The coffee was quite good. A couple other vegan offerings would be nice, like a vegan version of the egg sandwich. On the whole, a really nice, warm-feeling place to spend some time.
Progressive place. Great selection of good tea and other interesting plant based products.  Also seems like a good spot to take your laptop and be productive with all bases covered.
Great atmosphere for casual dining or working. Friendly staff, too!
I didn't get a chance to try the kombucha on tap but the coffee was really good.
Yummmmmmmm. Good vibes. Beautiful space! Love the new plants!
Amazing Coffee, Amazing Food and Amazing Staff. Friendly, Warm and excellent Vibes.
Such a cool spot. Great to catch up on some work or take a breather. Beautiful space full of plants! Love the matcha, pastries and kombucha on tap!
bomb smoothie nice insta aesthetic
Kombucha on tap, Coffee, Gluten free toasts and smoothies. Plants for sale, huge community space and backyard. The best coffee shop on Smith Street.
